label.value: Breast Cancer Clinical Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v6

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of breast cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Breast Cancer cNX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Breast cancer in which regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Breast Cancer cN0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Breast cancer with no regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Breast Cancer cN1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Breast cancer with metastasis to movable ipsilateral level I, II axillary lymph node(s).  (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Breast Cancer cN2 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Breast cancer with metastases in ipsilateral axillary lymph nodes fixed or matted, or in clinically apparent ipsilateral internal mammary nodes in the absence of clinically evident axillary lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)
A benign or malignant endocrine neoplasm that arises from the testis or the ovary.

label.value: Breast Cancer cN2a TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Breast cancer with metastases in ipsilateral level I, II axillary lymph nodes fixed to one another (matted) or to other structures. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Breast Cancer cN2b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Breast cancer with metastasis only in clinically apparent ipsilateral internal mammary nodes and in the absence of clinically evident axillary lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Breast Cancer cN3 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Breast cancer with metastasis in ipsilateral infraclavicular lymph node(s) with or without axillary lymph node involvement, or in clinically apparent ipsilateral internal mammary lymph node(s) and in the presence of clinically evident axillary lymph node metastasis; or metastasis in ipsilateral supraclavicular lymph node(s) with or without axillary or internal mammary lymph node involvement. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Breast Cancer cN3a TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Breast cancer with metastasis in ipsilateral infraclavicular lymph node(s). (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Breast Cancer cN3b TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Breast cancer with metastasis in ipsilateral internal mammary lymph node(s) and axillary lymph node(s). (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Breast Cancer cN3c TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Breast cancer with metastasis in ipsilateral supraclavicular lymph node(s). (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Breast Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v6

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of breast cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Breast Cancer cMX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Breast cancer in which the status of distant metastasis cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Breast Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Breast cancer in which there is no evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Breast Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Breast cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)
